&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adams Clinical is seeking a highly-motivated Psychologist or Mental Health Professional for a full-time role at our Watertown location. Individuals with clinical or research experience in psychiatry and/or Alzheimer’s Disease are highly encouraged to apply.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinician – Rater is responsible for conducting structured clinical interviews, diagnostic evaluations, neuropsychological assessments, and standardized rating scales to assess symptoms across a range of psychiatric and neurological conditions, including depression, anxiety, schizophrenia, ADHD, substance use disorders, and Alzheimer’s disease. In this role, the Clinician – Rater supports psychiatry and neurology clinical trials by determining participant eligibility through comprehensive clinical assessments and prescreening activities. The Clinician – Rater works closely with a multidisciplinary research team in a fast-paced clinical research environment to support high-quality data collection and successful trial execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct clinical interviews, diagnostic assessments, and standardized rating scales for psychiatry and neurology clinical trials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate symptoms and track clinical change across conditions including depression, anxiety, schizophrenia, substance use disorders, and Alzheimer’s disease&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain inter-rater reliability and adherence to standardized assessment procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with Good Clinical Practice (GCP) and regulatory requirements in a fast-paced research environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting reliable, efficient, high-quality clinical assessments in the context of a fast-paced clinical research setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrating curiosity and enthusiasm for learning new assessments and working with diverse populations across a variety of psychiatric and neurological indications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively incorporating feedback to grow skills and strengthen performance over time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working collaboratively with a multidisciplinary team to support smooth study execution and protocol compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum of a master’s degree and licensure / license-eligible to practice in a psychology-related role: e.g., psychology, social work, counseling.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
