&lt;p&gt;If you’re passionate about making an impact in clinical research and want to be part of a collaborative, mission-driven organization, we’d love to have you on our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adams Clinical is seeking applicants for the Mental Health Technician role within our inpatient research facility at our Watertown location. Mental Health Tech plays an essential role in ensuring participant safety and maintaining a therapeutic environment within our overnight inpatient research facility. This position supports ongoing clinical trials by providing direct care, supervision, and engagement with research participants under the guidance of the In-patient Unit Manager, Clinical Research Coordinators, and the Principal Investigator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The MHT also assists with basic clinical and laboratory tasks, contributing to protocol adherence and overall research integrity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide therapeutic interaction and manage behavioral changes using verbal de-escalation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review handoff reports and prepare detailed shift documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm unit transitions, assessments, and research visits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct wellness checks every 15 minutes and ensure proper documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supervise smoke breaks, assist with meals (especially weekends), and evening hygiene routines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support or co-facilitate scheduled activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor, assist, and document medication administration.&lt;/li&gt;
